answers.answer: Can mean preeclampsia. That's why they're doing the more in depth test. It's probably nothing but I would read up on preeclampsia and the risks it presents just so you're prepared for the possibility.
In order for it to be true pre-eclampsia, your blood pressure will be high too. If it's just the protein, then your Dr will just keep a close eye on your blood pressure.
She told me that she will move my c section date up if there is protein present. I just want my baby to be healthy
My blood pressure was high today. Its usually low like 120/60 but today it was 150/80

I had to do the same thing at 18 weeks due I high blood pressure and protein in my urine. Everything will be okay :) I know it's really scary but don't stress yourself out, it won't help your blood pressure or your baby any. And I do not recommend reading on it, there is too much misinformation out there. If you have any questions ask your dr or midwife.
